.TH LGPD_CRAWLER 1 "March 2026" "python3-lgpd-crawler" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lgpd_crawler \- audit databases and filesystems for personal and sensitive data
.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lgpd_crawler
[
.B \-\-config
.I FILE
]
[
.B \-\-web
]
[
.B \-\-port
.I PORT
]
[
.B \-\-tenant
.I NAME
]
[
.B \-\-technician
.I NAME
]
.
.P
The actual entry point is usually:
.br
.RS 4
.B python main.py
[
.I OPTIONS
]
.RE
.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B python3-lgpd-crawler
is a data discovery tool designed to help organizations comply with LGPD, GDPR, CCPA and related regulations by scanning databases, filesystems and other data sources for personal and sensitive data.
It uses configurable regular expressions and an ML classifier to identify potential PII, stores only metadata in a local SQLite database, and produces Excel reports and a sensitivity/risk heatmap PNG.
.
.P
The application can be run as a one\-shot CLI tool or as a long\-running web API with a simple dashboard.
Each scan run is stored as a session with optional
.I tenant/customer
and
.I technician/operator
tags for attribution.
.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI "\-\-config " FILE
Path to the configuration file (YAML or JSON).
Defaults to
.IR config.yaml .
Used both for one\-shot audits and to resolve API options when starting the web server.
.
.TP
.B \-\-web
Start the REST API server instead of running a one\-shot audit.
When this flag is set the process does not run a scan automatically; scans are triggered via HTTP (for example with
.BR curl (1)).
.
.TP
.BI "\-\-port " PORT
Port for the API when
.B \-\-web
is set.
Defaults to
.IR 8088 .
Ignored in one\-shot mode.
The effective port may also be overridden by
.B api.port
in the configuration file.
.
.TP
.B \-\-reset\-data
Dangerous maintenance operation that wipes all scan sessions, findings and failures from the SQLite database, deletes generated Excel reports and heatmap PNGs under
.I report.output_dir
and records a single row in the
.I data_wipe_log
table with the time and reason of the wipe.
When this flag is used, no scan is started; the process exits after the reset completes or fails.
.
.TP
.BI "\-\-tenant " NAME
Optional tenant or customer name for the scan in CLI (one\-shot) mode.
This value is stored as
.I tenant_name
on the scan session, appears on the web dashboard and reports list, and is written to the
.I "Report info"
sheet in the Excel report.
.
.TP
.BI "\-\-technician " NAME
Optional technician or operator name responsible for the scan in CLI (one\-shot) mode.
This value is stored as
.I technician_name
on the scan session, appears on the web dashboard and reports list, and is written to the
.I "Report info"
sheet in the Excel report.
.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B CONFIG_PATH
Path to the configuration file used by the web API.
When the server is started with
.B \-\-web
and
.B \-\-config
is not provided, the application loads configuration from
.B CONFIG_PATH
if set, or from
.IR config.yaml
in the current working directory.
.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I config.yaml
Default configuration file containing
.B targets
(databases, filesystems, APIs, shares), file scan options, report output directory and API settings.
.
.TP
.I audit_results.db
Local SQLite database where scan sessions, findings and failures are stored.
The path is controlled by
.B sqlite_path
in the configuration.
.
.TP
.I Relatorio_Auditoria_*.xlsx
Excel reports generated for each session, written under the directory specified by
.B report.output_dir
in the configuration.
.
.TP
.I heatmap_*.png
Sensitivity/risk heatmap images generated for each session, saved in the same directory as the Excel reports.
.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS One\-shot CLI scans
.TP
Minimal scan using the default configuration:
.RS
.B python main.py \-\-config config.yaml
.RE
.
.TP
.TP
Reset local history (dangerous) by wiping scan sessions, findings and generated reports:
.RS
.B python main.py \-\-config config.yaml \-\-reset\-data
.RE
.
.TP
Scan tagged with tenant and technician metadata:
.RS
.B python main.py \-\-config config.yaml \-\-tenant "Acme Corp" \-\-technician "Alice Silva"
.RE
.
.SS Running the web API
.TP
Start the API on port 8088:
.RS
.B python main.py \-\-config config.yaml \-\-web \-\-port 8088
.RE
.
.TP
Set the configuration file via
.B CONFIG_PATH
and start the server:
.RS
.nf
export CONFIG_PATH=/etc/lgpd\-audit/config.yaml
python main.py \-\-web \-\-port 8088
.fi
.RE
.
.SS Using the API with curl
.TP
Start a full audit with default metadata:
.RS
.nf
curl \-X POST http://localhost:8088/scan
.fi
.RE
.
.TP
Start a full audit tagged with tenant and technician:
.RS
.nf
curl \-X POST http://localhost:8088/scan \\
  \-H "Content\-Type: application/json" \\
  \-d '{ "tenant": "Acme Corp", "technician": "Alice Silva" }'
.fi
.RE
.
.TP
Check scan status:
.RS
.nf
curl http://localhost:8088/status
.fi
.RE
.
.TP
Download the latest Excel report:
.RS
.nf
curl \-o report.xlsx http://localhost:8088/report
.fi
.RE
.
.TP
Download the latest heatmap PNG:
.RS
.nf
curl \-o heatmap.png http://localhost:8088/heatmap
.fi
.RE
.
.TP
Download the latest audit log file:
.RS
.nf
curl \-o audit.log http://localhost:8088/logs
.fi
.RE
.
.TP
Download report and heatmap for a specific session:
.RS
.nf
curl \-o report_20250301.xlsx \\
  "http://localhost:8088/reports/a1b2c3d4\-20250301_143022"

curl \-o heatmap_20250301.png \\
  "http://localhost:8088/heatmap/a1b2c3d4\-20250301_143022"
.fi
.RE
.
.TP
Download the audit log that contains a specific session id:
.RS
.nf
curl \-o audit_20250301.log \\
  "http://localhost:8088/logs/a1b2c3d4\-20250301_143022"
.fi
.RE
.
.SH INSTALLATION
To install this man page system\-wide on a typical Linux or BSD system:
.PP
.RS
.nf
sudo cp docs/lgpd_crawler.1 /usr/local/share/man/man1/
sudo mandb            # or "sudo makewhatis" on some BSD systems
.fi
.RE
.
After installation, you can view it with:
.PP
.RS
.B man lgpd_crawler
.RE
.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR python (1),
.BR curl (1),
the project README and USAGE documentation in the source tree.

